!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

vigorous /ˈvɪɡərəs/

1. ADJ Vigorous physical activities involve using a lot of energy, usually to do short and repeated actions. 用力的 

例： Very vigorous exercise can increase the risk of heart attacks. 耗费大量体力的运动会增加心脏病发作的风险。 

2. vigorously ADV 用力地 [ADV after v] 

例： He shook his head vigorously. 他用力地摇了摇头。 

3. ADJ A vigorous person does things with great energy and enthusiasm. A vigorous campaign or activity is done with great energy and enthusiasm. 精力充沛的 (人); 强有力的 (运动、活动) 

例： Theodore Roosevelt was a strong and vigorous politician. 西奥多·罗斯福是一位身体强壮、精力充沛的政治家。 

4. vigorously ADV 强烈地 [ADV with v] 

例： The police vigorously denied that excessive force had been used. 警方坚决否认曾过度使用武力。

</div>

